Project guardrails for the crypto trading monitor platform:

- This platform is crypto-only.
- MVP is spot-only, one exchange provider, one market per run, backtest-first.
- Do not introduce futures, perpetual funding, replay, or live trading into MVP work unless explicitly requested.

ARCHITECTURAL GUARDRAILS
- Keep the system market-centric, not symbol-centric.
- Use exchange + market context consistently.
- Keep exchange-specific logic inside adapters.
- Keep strategy engine, risk engine, execution engine, journal, analytics, and ingestion clearly separated.

EXECUTION GUARDRAILS
- Strategies return TradeIntent only.
- Execution engine creates orders and fills.
- Fills are execution truth.
- Position is derived state.
- Trade is a round-trip journal entity from first opening to full close.

OBSERVABILITY GUARDRAILS
- Every important trading action must be traceable through events.
- reason_code, reason_text, indicator_snapshot, signal_context, candle_context, and risk_context must be preserved where relevant.
- correlation_id and causation_id must be complete enough to reconstruct event chains.
- Data quality issues must be evented and visible.

MVP EXECUTION RULES
- Candle-based execution only.
- Default fill logic must stay deterministic.
- Market orders only unless explicitly expanded later.
- Fees and slippage must remain configurable and testable.

QUALITY GUARDRAILS
- Do not expand scope before correctness and tests are solid.
- Prefer hardening over feature sprawl.
- Preserve consistency between backend models, API contracts, and frontend types.